cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper deals with aspect-based sentiment analysis (ABSA) using deep learning techniques and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and machine learning techniques for language processing. The paper also employs transfer learning and fine-tuning methods, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with finance-specific annotations, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as financial data is often sensitive and requires secure handling. Finally, the paper deals with classification and regression tasks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as these tasks are often used in information retrieval systems.
